and shew them the fethers of the
Bustarde, and so to please them.
The wife prayed hir husband (or
he wente) to fetche in a blocke to
the fyre: and in the meane space
she dyd put out all the Bustardes
fethers, and dyd put in the goose
fethers. The man takynge hys
poake or bag, went to the
gentlemens seruauntes and sayde,$] I
pray you be not angrye wyth mee
for you shall see here that I had a 
bustard, for here be the fethers: [$&
<P B5V>
he opened his bag, and did shake
out the goose fethers, The gentle
